    "narrative": "For the April 22 slate, the Austin Waves offense is primed for a high-output performance, anchored by the elite tier of **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (77.88). **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a potent combination of a favorable matchup against Michael Wacha and a significant dynamic platoon advantage, further buoyed by favorable wind conditions. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** is in an ideal spot against Tyler Mahle, where his base projection is elevated by strong SP skill indicators and his prominent #2 spot in the order. **Jackson Merrill** also warrants special attention; despite a matchup against Tomoyuki Sugano, his score of 75.10 is driven by a massive 14% park factor boost and a strong platoon alignment, making him a high-leverage start for our Roto categories.\n\nWe are paying close attention to the bottom of the order and bench management today, particularly with **Nasim Nunez** (67.95) serving as a high-upside play against the struggling Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez. **Nasim Nunez**\u2019s sprint speed potential makes him a critical asset for our scarcity-driven SB strategy. Among the bench, **Brady House** (56.17) was the most difficult exclusion; he projected well against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez but ultimately fell behind the consolidated utility value provided by **Marcell Ozuna** and the specific positional flexibility of the starters. We are currently operating under a \"Lineup Pending\" status for most of our squad; while we have forecasted the optimal batting positions, any late-breaking news regarding **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** or **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** shifting down in the order could necessitate a recalibration of their efficiency scores. **Dominic Smith** remains our lowest-graded starter (54.77) and represents the primary candidate to pull if a high-performing bench piece like **Nolan Schanuel** or **Coby Mayo** earns a promotion to a more favorable spot in their respective lineups.",
